Entity CalendarEntry

Action perform_calendar_entry_creation
  EventInput
    space_id, title, datetime_start, datetime_end   required
    description, task_id                             optional
  BusinessRules
    - space_id must reference an Active Space owned by the actor
    - datetime_end must be > datetime_start
    - If task_id provided: task must exist in the same space
  Steps
    - Create CalendarEntry record with status = Active
  SideEffects
    - Trigger create_automatic_note with type = calendar_entry_created
  ActionResult
    calendar_entry_id   UUID

Action perform_calendar_entry_update
  EventInput
    calendar_entry_id                                       required
    title, description, datetime_start, datetime_end, task_id   optional
  BusinessRules
    - At least one field must be provided
    - If both datetime_start and datetime_end provided: end must be > start
    - If only datetime_end provided: must be > existing datetime_start
    - If only datetime_start provided: must be < existing datetime_end
    - If task_id provided: task must exist in the same space
  Steps
    - Update provided fields on CalendarEntry record
  SideEffects
    - None
  ActionResult
    calendar_entry_id   UUID
    updated_fields      string[]

Action perform_calendar_entry_archive
  EventInput
    calendar_entry_id   required
  Steps
    - Update CalendarEntry status to Archived
  SideEffects
    - None
  ActionResult
    calendar_entry_id   UUID

Action notify_already_archived
  Steps
    - No state change
  Outcome
    NoAction    CALENDAR_ENTRY_ALREADY_ARCHIVED

Action reject_request
  Steps
    - No state change
  Outcome
    NoAction    REQUEST_REJECTED
